 to use his fame to intervene in political, social, and scientific matters. At times, Urey succeeded, including when he helped create the fields of isotope geochemistry and cosmochemistry. But other endeavors, such as his promotion of world governance of atomic weapons, failed. By exploring those efforts, as well as Urey’s evolution from farm boy to scientific celebrity, we can discern broader changes in the social and intellectual landscape of twentieth-century America. More than a life story, this book immerses readers in the struggles and triumphs of not only an extraordinary man, but also his extraordinary times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aChemistszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  a20th-century science.  aChurch of the Brethren.  aManhattan Project.  aProject Apollo.  abiography.  achemistry.  acold war science.  aplanetary science.  ascience and religion.  aspace exploration.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831107119430 cprintz978022666208440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226662114423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226662114/original  a978-3-11-061017-8  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deG